Center: US National Nuclear Data Center, Brookhaven, USA
title: Interaction of High-Energy Protons With Indium

x4codes.hlp: Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory, Livermore, CA, United States of America

x4freetext: INTERACTION OF HIGH-ENERGY PROTONS WITH INDIUM
THE TARGET ASSEMBLY CONSISTED OF A 0.003-IN. INDIUM
TARGET FOIL (>99.9% INDIUM) AND A 0.003-IN. ALUMINUM
MONITOR FOIL. THREE 0.001-IN. ALUMINUM GUARD FOILS
WERE USED TO SEPARATE AND COVER THE FOILS AS A PROTEC-
TION FROM RECOIL AND SECONDARY PARTICLES.
IT WAS ESTIMATED THAT THE OVER-ALL UNCERTAINTY IN THE
CORRECTIONS DUE TO ERRORS IN COUNTING EFFICIENCIES,
COUNTING STATISTICS, MONITOR CROSS SECTION, ETC., WAS
ABOUT +-30%. THE CROSS SECTIONS FOR THE NUCLIDES
CD-107, CD-109, AND IN-109 WERE LESS ACCURATELY KNOWN
